A dog breeder who claimed almost £17,000 in benefits claiming she had difficult walking was caught when investigators filmed her jogging with her prized Collies in a show ring.

Susan Malpas conned the taxpayer out of thousands in disability living allowance over six years - even saying she needed help leaving her house.

But undercover fraud investigators from the Department of Work and Pensions (DWP) filmed the 62-year-old parading her Collie at a dog show on August 31 last year.

